   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Educate Internally Displaced Anglophone Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Two years into the Anglophone Crisis, hundreds have been recorded dead, over a thousand homes burned , dozens of schools attacked and over 250,000 people have fled their homes. Denis Miki Foundation is working with several local communities affected by the crisis to ensure that children are educated by finding educational opportunities and promoting online classrooms for Internally Displaced Children or those still living in conflict areas so as to ensure their proper education.</narrative>
  </description>
